    caption: [Families of evolutionarily related genes in the genome of Bacillus subtilis. The largest gene family in this bacterium consists of 77 genes coding for varieties of a class of membrane transport proteins called ABC transporters, which are found in all three domains of the living world. (Adapted from F. Kunst et al., Nature 390:249–256, 1997.) 20],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
