  "1-22": (
    caption: [Phagocytosis. An electron micrograph of a mammalian phagocytic white blood cell (a neutrophil) ingesting a bacterium that is in the process of dividing. Only the part of the cell that is extending surface protrusions to engulf the bacterium is shown. (Courtesy of Dorothy Bainton.)],
