  "1-33": (
    caption: [An assortment of single-cell eukaryotes. The drawings are done to different scales, but in each case the scale bar represents 10 μm. The organisms in (A), (C), and (G) are ciliates; (B) is a heliozoan; (D) is an amoeba; (E) is a dinoflagellate; and (F) is a euglenoid. (Courtesy of Michael Sleigh, from M.A. Sleigh, Biology of Protozoa. Edinburgh: Edward Arnold, 1973.) (D) (A) (B) (C) (E) (F) (G)],
