    caption: [Caenorhabditis elegans, the first multicellular organism to have its complete genome sequence determined. This nematode is only about 1 mm long and normally lives in the soil. Most individuals are hermaphrodites, producing both eggs and sperm. (Courtesy of Maria Gallegos, University of Wisconsin, Madison.) 0.2 mm],
