  "1-43": (
    caption: [Drosophila melanogaster. (A) A normal adult Drosophila fruit fly. Molecular genetic studies of this fly have provided the main key to understanding how all animals develop from a fertilized egg into an adult. (B) A mutant adult fly, in which a mutation in a regulatory DNA sequence has caused genes for leg formation to be abnormally activated in positions normally reserved for antennae; as a result, legs have developed where antennae should be. (A, Edward B. Lewis, Courtesy of the Archives, California Institute of Technology; B, courtesy of Matthew Scott.) 20 µm],
