  "1-45": (
    caption: [The early stages of normal frog development. These drawings show the development of a Rana pipiens tadpole from a fertilized egg. The entire process takes place outside the mother, making the mechanisms involved readily accessible for experimental studies. (From W. Shumway, Anat. Rec. 78:139–147, 1940. With permission from John Wiley & Sons.)],
